NTFS permissions in IT help desk

 It’s Not Just “Access Denied.” It’s Security. 🔒

We’ve all been there. A user tickets in: “I can’t open this folder.”

The quick fix? Grant “Full Control” and move on. 🛑

But as IT professionals, we know that NTFS permissions are the backbone of Windows security hygiene. 
Misconfigured permissions aren’t just an inconvenience; they’re a vulnerability.

Quick Refresher for Help Desk Heroes:

✅ Least Privilege Principle: Only grant the permissions necessary for the task. Read-only is often enough.
✅ Inheritance Matters: Understand how permissions flow from parent folders. Breaking inheritance should be a deliberate choice, not a default.
✅ Deny vs. Allow: Remember that “Deny” always takes precedence. 
A single “Deny” entry can override multiple “Allow” entries, causing confusing access issues.
✅ Groups > Users: Assign permissions to Security Groups, not individual users. It makes management scalable and audit-friendly.

Next time you see an “Access Denied” error, take the extra minute to audit the effective permissions. 
